ec2.userdata:
#!/bin/bash
PRIVATEIP=$(curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/local-ipv4)
rm -f /home/cloud_user/.ICEauthority
if grep 'adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com' /etc/hosts
then
  # update IP and force hostname set
  sed -i "/^# Cloud Server Hostname mapping/,$ s/^.*adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com/$PRIVATEIP adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com/g" /etc/hosts
  hostname adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com
else
  if [ -d /etc/sysconfig ]
  then
    echo "HOSTNAME=adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com" >> /etc/sysconfig/network
  fi
  echo "adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com" > /etc/hostname
  echo "$PRIVATEIP   adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com" >> /etc/hosts
  hostname adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com
fi

if [ $(command -v systemctl) ]
then
  hostnamectl set-hostname adanvazquez2c.mylabserver.com
  systemctl daemon-reload
  sed -i 's/^Host 172.*/Host PRIVATEIP/' /etc/ssh/ssh_config
  systemctl restart linux-academy-websh
  if [ $(command -v vncserver) ]
  then
    rm -rf /home/cloud_user/.cache
    systemctl restart vncserver@:1
  fi
else
  killall node
  sleep 10
  service linux-academy-websh restart
fi
